I have never been interested in reggae music and Trinidad and Tobago’s flag. But when I saw the music video of Morissah “Madd Freestyle” it made me want to research more about her. So here we go,

About Morissah’s life she lived in Rose Hall (the other side of Red House countryside).At age eight, she decided to become successful. To do that, she taught herself how to write and produce her own songs.

In 2006, Morissah auditioned for So You Want To Be Brass 2 and was awarded the $1 million prize for her performance. “For my own wanted to be something special, I got that role,” she said. But she didn’t accept name that title. For she was labeled by locals ornament for people to ignore.

For five years she wasn’t no where near her music career. She was always in the prison and she was always known as being the of those insolent women—a “man place”. But them was good for her, because here in Trinidad and Tobago “it’s a woman’s world”. So as she was in prison, one of the inmate reserved her good attention to learn write her music. More, her husband wanted her to keep that job
